race.description: Move To Strike At Lovatsville Hcp
race.comment: BLACK RUN (1) comes down from Sydney in good form, not taking long to find winning form with a tough victory in a BM78 at Randwick second up. Suspect he'll be fitter again out to the suitable 2400m and the local brigade doesn't look overly strong. HOT TOO GO (13) ran out a good winner over a well backed favourite at Moonee Valley last time out. Can't see the trip being an issue and he'll get every chance to run it out from an ideal gate. ALMAIRAC (9) can mix his form but was close up over this route last time out, albeit in a very slowly run race. Tricky draw but is suited this level. ALMA RISE (2) hasn't fired this time in but will naturally find this much easier than the G3 Bendigo Cup last time, not disgraced there.
